  "author_association": "MEMBER",
  "active_lock_reason": null,
  "body": "When inserting blocks into the database, we first mark the new block as a head https://github.com/ethereum/go-ethereum/blob/master/core/chain_manager.go#L512 and only then write the actualy block itself https://github.com/ethereum/go-ethereum/blob/master/core/chain_manager.go#L520. This seems a data race, as any query in between the two operations will read invalid state (i.e. the head block will not exist). I can rework this within my eth/63 PR, just wanted to check if it's the case or I'm misunderstanding something.\n",
